OL,3,CHotel owner on 'crippling' reality of
OL,4,Ctrying to survive in cost of living
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FHotel owners in Torbay say they are
OL,8,Fexperiencing the slowest start to a
OL,9,Fsummer season for many years - and
OL,10,Fsome fear the industry could come
OL,11,Fclose to collapse if nothing changes.
OL,13,FGuest houses are feeling the impact as
OL,14,Fpeople either go abroad, or opt for a
OL,15,Fshorter break than usual.
OL,17,FCatharine Hooper, who runs the
OL,18,FBrantwood guest house, said the cost
OL,19,Fof living crisis is "the worst thing
OL,20,Fthat's happened in 15 years".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/4
